<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,978,1722]" pageId="4" pageNumber="575">
Head with tegument black and opaque. Frons (
<date box="[674,726,978,1002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="575" value="1940-10">
<number box="[674,703,978,1002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="575" value="40.0">40</number>
x
</date>
) punctate on sides. Vertex with sparse, black pubescence. Eyes finely granulate. Upper ocular lobes (width = 
<quantity box="[665,752,1014,1038]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="575" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
) separated from one another by 
<number box="[1116,1151,1014,1038]" pageId="4" pageNumber="575" value="3.5">3.5</number>
times the width of a lobe (distance between lobes = 
<quantity box="[473,569,1050,1074]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="575" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
). Antennae (male) black, reaching the apical fourth of the elytra. Scape thickened toward the apex, finely, densely punctate, covered by short, black hairs, with a few much longer hairs; longer than antennomere III. Antennomeres III-VI with tufts of dense black hairs on the inner margin apically, gradually thicker and longer in the direction of VI. Antennomeres VII-IX with length gradually decreasing. Antennomeres X and XI missing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,978,1722]" pageId="4" pageNumber="575">Prothorax reddish-yellow, except on anterior border of the underside, and perimeter of the procoxa. Pronotum with four dark spots: very small ones close to the anterior margin; the others black and larger, close to the basal edge. Pronotal surface opaque, smooth in the center and with very sparse hairs laterally. Sides of prothorax smooth. Prosternum punctate with sparse, white hairs. Scutellum black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,978,1722]" pageId="4" pageNumber="575">Elytra entirely yellow with contrasting dark punctures; outer costa more projected than the inner. Elytral extremities rounded.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,978,1722]" box="[199,758,1446,1470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="575">Thoracic sterna black. Urosternites reddish-black.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
